HEADWORD: Affirmant
<hw>Af*firm"ant</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧f*f⟦etil⟧rm"⟦ait⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>affirmans</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>, p. pr. See
<er>Affirm</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who affirms or
asserts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who affirms, instead of taking
an oath.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Affirmation</ent>⟦br⟧
